                     <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Solved Problem: </strong></span>
                        The dose of a drug is 20 &mu;g/kg of body weight. What would be the dose for a 200 pound patient?</p>
                    <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Approach: </strong></span>Convert the pounds to kilograms, use the equation used for calculating drug dosage based on weight.</p>
                    <div class="formuale"> $$ Patient' s \ Weight (kg) = { 200 \over 2.2 } = 90.9 \ Kg $$</div>
                    <div class="formulae"><p>  $$ { Patient's \ Dose \ (&mu;g)  =  Patient's \ Weight (kg) \times } {  Drug \ dose \ (&mu;g) \over 1 \ (kg)} $$</p></div>
                    <div class="formulae"><p>  $$ { Patient's \ Dose \ (&mu;g)  =  90.9 \ (kg) \times } {  20 \ (&mu;g) \over 1 \ (kg)} $$</p></div>
                    <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Answer: </strong></span>1818 &mu;g</p>
                    
                    </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                    <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Solved Problem: </strong></span>
                    The dose of clindamycin for treating a skin abscess is 8-16 mg/kg/day divided into three or four equal doses. Capsule strength available includes 150 mg and 300 mg. What strength, directions and how many capsules should be dispensed for a 10 day course for an 80-lb child.
                    </p>
                    <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Approach: </strong></span>
                    Convert the pounds to kilograms, use the equation used for calculating drug dosage based on weight.
                    </p>
                    <div class="formuale"> $$ Patient' s \ Weight (kg) = { 80 \over 2.2 } = 36.4 \ Kg $$</div> 
                    <div class="formulae"><p>  $$ { Patient's \ Dose \ (mg)  =  Patient's \ Weight (kg) \times } {  Drug \ dose \ (mg) \over 1 \ (kg)} $$</p></div>
                    <div class="formulae"><p>  $$ { Patient's \ Dose \ (mg)  =  36.4 (kg) \times } {  8 - 16 \ (m;g) \over 1 \ (kg)} $$</p></div>
                    <div class= "formulae"><p> $$ { Patient's \ Dose \ (mg) = 291.2 mg - 582.4 mg } $$</p></div>
                     
                     <p>The above dose range has to be divided into 3-4 equal doses. </p>
                    
                    <div class= "formulae"> <p> $$ { Patient's \ Dose \ (mg) } = { 291.2 mg \over 3-4} - {  582.4 mg \over 3-4}$$</p></div>
                    <div class = "formulae"> <p> $$ {Patient's \ Dose \ (mg) } = { 97 - 194 \ mg \ po \ tid \ or \ 73 - 146 \ po \ qid } $$</p></div>
                     <p>For this patient, 150 mg capsules, taken three times daily will comply with the dosing guidelines.</p>
                    <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Answer: </strong>Clindamycin 150 mg, # 30 capsules</span></p>
                    <p>Take 1 capsule by mouth three times a day.</p>
                    </td>
                    </tr>
