                    <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Solved Problem: </strong></span>A 6’ man weighs 195 lb. What is his ABW and his IBW in kg?</p>
                    <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Approach: </strong></span>Convert the pounds to kilograms, use the equation used for calculating IBW for a male</p>
                    
                    <div class="formulae"><p> $$ Patient's \ Weight \ (kg) \ = { 195 \over 2.2 } = 88.6  \ kg \ (ABW) $$</p></div>
                    <div class="formulae"><p> $$ Male: {50 \ kg + (2.3 \ kg)(12) } = 77.6 \ kg \ (IBW) $$</p></div>
                    <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Answer: </strong></span>88.6 kg, 77.6 kg</p>
